  "description": "A two-compartment, dual-circuit refrigerator from the brand Bosch is an advanced class solution with a useful capacity of 363 liters. The appliance is suitable for medium and some large families, featuring standard dimensions of 203x60x66.5 cm. The model features internal sensor control with an intuitive selection of temperature modes and the ability to activate additional options, including rapid cooling or freezing. The unit belongs to the Full No Frost category of devices, meaning that in both compartments, a fan ensures air circulation and removes excess moisture, eliminating the need for manual defrosting. The Bosch KGN392LDFG refrigerator includes a 103-liter freezer compartment optimally placed at the bottom of the body. Here, there are three pull-out transparent boxes and an included ice tray. The freezing capacity is 10 kg per day, and the autonomous cold preservation period (during power issues) lasts up to 15 hours. In the 260-liter fridge compartment, there are four open sections, a suspended bottle shelf, and two VitaFresh drawers, including a container for vegetables and fruits, as well as a fresh zone where the temperature is maintained at around 0 degrees Celsius (primarily recommended for meat and fish). Worth special mention is the inverter compressor, which enhances the accuracy of temperature settings, is more reliable, quieter (with a noise level of up to 35 dB in this case), and more economical — class D with a consumption of 203 kWh.",
